cvmx_gmx::_tx::_stat4

GMX_TX_STAT4 = GMX_TX_STATS_HIST1 (64) / GMX_TX_STATS_HIST0 (<64)

Notes:

  • Packet length is the sum of all data transmitted on the wire for the given packet including packet data, pad bytes, fcs bytes, pause bytes, and jam bytes. The octect counts do not include PREAMBLE byte or EXTEND cycles.
  • Cleared either by a write (of any value) or a read when GMX_TX_STATS_CTL[RD_CLR] is set
  • Counters will wrap
